 # Strandspace
+
## What Strandspace is

Strandspace is a local-first memory and skill layer for agents that reduces repeated token usage by recalling reusable constructs from compact cues before escalating to an LLM.

## What Strandspace is not

Strandspace does not replace large language models or AI. It serves as a recall and composition layer to assist specialized agents in reducing repeated work.

## Why test it inside agents

Testing Strandspace within an agent framework (e.g., OpenClaw, LangGraph, or similar) helps measure how well it improves latency, reduces token usage, and facilitates agent skill composition during recurring tasks.
